<div class="border">
<div class="page">
<h1>Categories</h1>

<ul>
<% for category in @categories %>
  <li>
    <h3><%= link_to h(category.name), category %></h3>
    <ul>
      <% category.sources.each do |source| %>
        <li><%= link_to h(source.name), source_path(source) %></li>
      <% end %>
    </ul>
  </li>
<% end %>
</ul>

Categories are a way to organize sources.  You can define a category for 
your sources by editing a source.<br/>
<br/>
<%= link_to 'Add a new category', new_category_path %>
</div>
</div>